result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (6th) [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (6th) [Modifiers: Habitual Criminality] was dismissed by the court.

  • Larissa A Gudleske was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consec to all other sentences.  Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

superMiscConds.notes: $250 DNA surcharge remitted. $1519  to be collected by the Dept of Corrections.  Court financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.  Restitution shall be paid pursuant to separate court order.  The balance remaining at release from prison be paid as a condition of extended supervision or parole at a rate determined by the supervising agent.

Defendant shall not use/possess alcohol, drug paraphernalia and/or controlled substances without a valid prescription & agent's written approval.  Do not drive a motor vehicle without valid DL and written approval of agent & IID. Do not enter any establishment whose primary purpose is alcohol. May not reside anywhere there is alcohol. May not touch any container containing alcohol.

supervisions.notes: IID restriction effective upon licensure for 36 mo.
